      <p>Male or Female.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="gender" data-choice="male" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 6rem;">Male</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="gender" data-choice="female" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 6rem;">Female</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  
  
  <!-- question 3 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="4">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>3. Do you have any family health history of any respiratory disease?</h1>
      <p>Some examples of respiratory diseases are Acute Bronchitis, Asthma, Bronchiectasis, Bronchiolitis, COPD, COVID 19, Influenza, Lung Cancer, Cycstic Fibrosis, Pertussis, Occupational Lung Diseases, Rhinosinusitis, Tuberculosis.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="familyHistory" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="familyHistory" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 4 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="5">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>4. Do you smoke or does anyone in your family smoke?</h1>
      <p>Smoking can increases your risk of lung disease by damaging your airways and the small air sacs (alveoli) found in your lungs.</p>
      <p>Source: <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/tobacco/data_statistics/fact_sheets/health_effects/effects_cig_smoking/index.htm#:~:text=1%2C2-,Smoking%20and%20Respiratory%20Disease,alveoli)%20found%20in%20your%20lungs.&text=Lung%20diseases%20caused%20by%20smoking,includes%20emphysema%20and%20chronic%20bronchitis.&text=Cigarette%20smoking%20causes%20most%20cases%20of%20lung%20cancer.">www.cdc.gov</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="smokingHistory" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="smokingHistory" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 5 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="6">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>5. Do you feel chest pain?</h1>
      <p>The possible causes of chest pain may be lung-related.</p>
      <p>Source: <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/chest-pain/symptoms-causes/syc-20370838">www.mayoclinic.org</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="chestPain" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="chestPain" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 6 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="7">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>6. Do you cough?</h1>
      <p>Coughing is one of the symptoms of many respiratory diseases.</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.webmd.com/lung/dont-ignore-breathing-problems#:~:text=A%20thick%2C%20wet%20cough%20can,well%20as%20they%20used%20to.">www.webmd.com</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="cough" data-choice="dry" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 14rem;">Yes. Dry Coughing.</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="cough" data-choice="productive" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 14rem;">Yes. Productive (wet) Coughing.</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="cough" data-choice="dry" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 14rem;">No.</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 7 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="8">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>7. Do you cough up blood?</h1>
      <p>The condition of coughing up blood (or Hemotypsis) indicates airway bleeding, and may be caused by many different respiratory diseases such as tuberculosis or pneumonia.</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemoptysis#:~:text=Hemoptysis%20is%20the%20coughing%20up,pneumonia%2C%20and%20certain%20cardiovascular%20conditions.">Wikipedia</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="coughingUpBlood" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="coughingUpBlood" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 8 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="9">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>8. Do you have a fever?</h1>
      <p>The CDC considers a person to have a fever when he or she has measured temperature of 100.4°F (38°C).</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.cdc.gov/quarantine/air/reporting-deaths-illness/definitions-symptoms-reportable-illnesses.html">www.cdc.gov</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="fever" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="fever" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 9 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="10">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>9. Do you experience rapid breathing?</h1>
      <p>In adult humans at rest, any respiratory rate between 12 and 20 breaths is normal and tachypnea is indicated by a rate greater than 20 breaths per minute.</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tachypnea#:~:text=Tachypnea%20is%20a%20respiration%20rate,resulting%20in%20abnormally%20rapid%20breathing.&text=In%20adult%20humans%20at%20rest,than%2020%20breaths%20per%20minute.">Wikipedia.</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="rapidBreathing" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="rapidBreathing" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 10 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="11">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>10. Do you experience shortness of breath?</h1>
      <p>Shortness of breath (or dyspnea) is often described as an intense tightening in the chest, air hunger, difficulty breathing, breathlessness or a feeling of suffocation.</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/symptoms/shortness-of-breath/basics/definition/sym-20050890#:~:text=Shortness%20of%20breath%20%E2%80%94%20known%20medically,breath%20in%20a%20healthy%20person.">Mayoclinic</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="shortnessOfBreath" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="shortnessOfBreath" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 11 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="12">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>11. Do you experience rapid heartbeat?</h1>
      <p>Tachycardia is the medical term for a heart rate over 100 beats per minute.</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/tachycardia/symptoms-causes/syc-20355127#:~:text=Tachycardia%20heartbeat,-In%20tachycardia%2C%20an&text=Tachycardia%20is%20the%20medical%20term,to%20have%20a%20fast%20heartbeat.">Mayoclinic</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="rapidHeartbeat" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="rapidHeartbeat" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 12 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="13">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>12. Do you experience wheezing?</h1>
      <p>Wheezing is a high-pitched whistling sound made while you breathe.</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.healthline.com/health/wheezing#:~:text=Wheezing%20is%20a%20high%2Dpitched,that%20requires%20diagnosis%20and%20treatment.">www.healthline.com</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="wheezing" data-choice="Y" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">Yes</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <button data-question="wheezing" data-choice="N" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 4rem;">No</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- question 13 -->
  <div class="question-container" data-number="14">
    <div class="question">
      <h1>13. How long your symptoms last?</h1>
      <p>Symptoms of some respiratory diseases like COVID 19 can last for months.</p>
      <p>Source: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/long-term-effects.html">www.cdc.gov</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="input">
      <div>
        <button data-question="duration" data-choice="<1 week" data-answer-type="choice" class="submit" style="width: 12rem;">Less than one week</button>
      </div>
      <div>
